article.description: Jordan Baker and Ahmad Caver scored 14 points apiece as Old Dominion surged past winless Dartmouth 59-47 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Old Dominion beats Dartmouth 59-47
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Jordan Baker and Ahmad Caver scored 14 points apiece as Old Dominion surged past winless Dartmouth 59-47 on Wednesday night. Baker was 4 of 10 from the field including four 3-pointers and Caver was 5 of 12 including five from distance. Brandan Stith added 11 points with six rebounds for the Monarchs (4-2) who had 10 team steals contributing to 16 Dartmouth turnovers. Old Dominion led by 11 at the break but Dartmouth was able to cut it to two, 43-41, on an Ian Carter 3-pointer with 7:42 to play. The Monarchs answered with a 14-6 surge capped by a Stith dunk to make it 57-47 with 15 seconds to play. Old Dominion took an early first-period lead on a Baker 3-pointer and had a 33-22 advantage at the break. Evan Boudreaux scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead the Big Green (0-5).
